The White House held a press briefing on September 30, 2009. During the briefing, White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs discussed several topics, including the format of a meeting President Obama would have with advisors on Afghanistan, the political climate surrounding the Afghanistan review, the President's views on the war in Afghanistan, the President's stance on climate change legislation, and the upcoming Copenhagen talks. Gibbs also addressed questions about health care reform, Iran's nuclear program, and the firing of Peter Galbraith from the U.N. mission in Afghanistan.